Designation: Action Painter - Drip Master of Chaos and Control
Bio: Jackson Pollock (1912-1956), American painter who revolutionized abstract expressionism through his 'drip' technique. Student of Thomas Hart Benton, he transformed Benton's rhythmic approach into pure abstraction. His technique of pouring and dripping paint onto horizontal canvases created 'action paintings' that captured movement and unconscious expression.
